headline: Black Friday Stock Sale: Down 12% to 25%, These 3 Dividend Stocks Are Great Bargain Buys Right Now
summary: Because of that, it's getting harder to find bargains or attractive income investments.  Shares of Alexandria Real Estate Equities (NYSE: ARE), Rexford Industrial Realty (NYSE: REXR), and W. P. Carey (NYSE: WPC) are down by between 12% and 25% this year, which has pushed their dividend yields higher.  Alexandria Real Estate Equities has lost about 12% of its value this year.
